<br>
Aary is harder than anything else inside that wing.  Except Ring of Vulak, which isn't even Velious era content.  The triplets can be hard if you can't figure out the tactics, and if you don't have a decent sized force, Nev might be out of your league.<br>
<br>
Also, Aary is geographically positioned such that he blocks you from entering the wing (obviously).  You can't get past him unless you kill him.<br>
<br>
So for a guild who couldn't do Aary, for them to enter NToV after someone else took the effort of killing the hardest mob is very wrong.  They haven't earned their way in.  <br>
<br>
Also, another relic of that era was the fact that when Aary popped, ALL the other dragons also popped.  There was no random 12 hour respawn thingy back then.  Nowadays, if you kill Aary on patch day, there is usually NOTHING alive except Dagarn the Destroyer (who also seems to pop on server up) and maybe 1 or 2 random dragons who popped.  So you put in the effort to kill the hardest mob in NToV and you don't get to reap the relative rewards of killing the other easier dragons.  So there's another reason why the rule makes sense--killing Aary gives you the &quot;right&quot; to those mobs as they spawn, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>as long as you don't go actively raiding other content when you have a NToV capable force online.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
There's still some reasons why it makes sense.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, 1 other one.<br>
<br>
Cause it's just damn respectful, and respect and happiness &gt; loot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hordainisonegreatshammy>hordainisonegreatshammy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pig<font color=#FF0000>?</font> Pig<font color=#FF0000>?</font></span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/3/03 2:24:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2045.topic&index=94>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dragonreborn.cc/albums/pictures/abn.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;Unrivaled Chaos&gt;</span><hr size=1> /huggles seke <p>MUCH LOVE <br>
